The paper discusses a new class of neural networks for learning representations from compressed random measurements of data, specifically images. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.IT.
